name: Sifan Hassan
summary: Dutch athlete Sifan Hassan has triumphed in the women's marathon at the 2024 Paris Olympics, marking her third gold medal of the games. Her victory in the grueling 26.2-mile race secured her as the only athlete to win the 5,000m, 10,000m, and marathon in a single Olympic cycle. Hassan's remarkable achievement cements her status as one of the greatest distance runners of all time. Despite facing challenges including a fall during the race, she persevered, showcasing her resilience and determination. The Netherlands star has come a long way from her humble beginnings as a refugee, inspiring athletes and fans alike with her extraordinary talent and unwavering spirit.

name: Emily Campbell
summary: Team GB's Emily Campbell, a weightlifting pioneer, has achieved great success, winning a bronze medal at the Paris Olympics. Her journey as a woman in the sport serves as an inspiration for others, highlighting how women's bodies are constantly changing. Campbell's victory has garnered attention for its significance on the next generation of weightlifters. Outside of her sporting accomplishments, the Olympic star has shared anecdotes about the lively atmosphere surrounding the games and her personal life. Celebrating her achievements, Team GB highlighted her distinctive hairstyle as they acknowledged her as the final medalist for the Paris Games. Campbell has even expressed interest in potentially participating in Strictly Come Dancing, showcasing her versatility and the impact she is making both on and off the field of play.

name: Thomas Bach
summary: Thomas Bach, the current president of the International Olympic Committee (IOC), has announced that he will step down in 2025. Bach, who has led the IOC since 2013, has been a controversial figure, particularly regarding his handling of the Tokyo Olympics during the COVID-19 pandemic and his stance on allowing transgender athletes to compete. Sebastian Coe, the former head of the London 2012 Olympics organizing committee, is considered a potential successor to Bach. Bach will leave the role after overseeing the 2024 Paris Games and the 2026 Winter Olympics in Milan-Cortina.

name: Alex Yee
summary: British triathlete Alex Yee has made headlines after achieving remarkable victories and honors. At the Paris 2024 Olympic Games, he staged an extraordinary comeback to clinch gold in the men's triathlon. His stunning performance has earned him widespread recognition, including a feature in British GQ and an interview with 220 Triathlon. Yee also played a pivotal role as part of the British team that secured bronze in the Mixed Team Relay at Loughborough University. In a show of community spirit, a bridge in Brockley was repainted "BrockYee" in his honor. Additionally, Yee and Bryony Page were chosen as Team GB's flagbearers at the closing ceremony. His achievements have made him a household name, with outlets such as Yahoo News UK and BBC celebrating his triumph. Yee's success has also led to his collaboration with the Brownlee brothers in a star-studded triathlon lineup.

name: Olympics 2028
summary: With the 2028 Olympics set to be held in Los Angeles, preparations are well underway. A quarter of Britons believe they have the potential to qualify for the Games, according to a YouGov survey. The city of Los Angeles is anticipating a surge in visitors and is hiring extensively for the event. Ticket reselling platforms like Viagogo are positioning themselves to secure a spot in the ticketing process. Forbes provides guidance on purchasing tickets for the 2028 Olympics. Despite Los Angeles' notorious traffic, Mayor Eric Garcetti aims for a "no-car Games." The Games will witness the emergence of new stars, with Paris 2024 serving as a potential stepping stone for athletes like Leon Marchand and Quincy Wilson. While breaking will not be featured in the 2028 Olympics, Australian breakdancer Raygun criticized the decision and defended herself against online trolls.
